tweet: @luxebytes I used ones with Indian ink in it and it worked well. Another trick i saw was if your paper is kinda glossy, try to put some matte transparent tape over the sensor right next to the blade. Apparently some paper produce to much glare for the sensor

name: 💮🎴 MikhailAsmo 🎴💮

tweet: @luxebytes Try putting some marker on the registration marks. Also when creating a file with Pixscan enabled, never decrease the registration mark's length. Silhouette machine really dont like it when you do that. To save space instead decrease the Inset

name: 💮🎴 MikhailAsmo 🎴💮
description: │█║│║▌║ 22 yrs old /🇫🇷/ #ActuallyAutistic / Independent Artist/ #krita & blender /Looking for work!/ I make shirts and masks  │█║│║▌║
tweet: I highly recommend to all of you to experiment and try out all the filters in order to discover what they do . I'm only showing the ones i use the most, but keep in mind there are 500+ filters in total, who do a ton of very cool stuff 🎉 13/15

name: 💮🎴 MikhailAsmo 🎴💮
description: │█║│║▌║ 22 yrs old /🇫🇷/ #ActuallyAutistic / Independent Artist/ #krita & blender /Looking for work!/ I make shirts and masks  │█║│║▌║
tweet: The Chromatic Aberration filter. Pretty self explanatory. Its in the Degradation category 12/15 https://t.co/capsvp6vkz

name: 💮🎴 MikhailAsmo 🎴💮
description: │█║│║▌║ 22 yrs old /🇫🇷/ #ActuallyAutistic / Independent Artist/ #krita & blender /Looking for work!/ I make shirts and masks  │█║│║▌║
tweet: Gold-Meinel and Inverse diffusion are essentially the same, the only difference is that Inverse diffusion is a little bit more subtle than Gold-Meinel. Both are in the Details category 11/15

name: 💮🎴 MikhailAsmo 🎴💮
description: │█║│║▌║ 22 yrs old /🇫🇷/ #ActuallyAutistic / Independent Artist/ #krita & blender /Looking for work!/ I make shirts and masks  │█║│║▌║
tweet: Next is the series of  [Sharpen] filters, particularly the Gold-Meinel one and the Inverse diffusion one . Very useful when upping the sharpness of down scaled images (in the exemple the Gold meinel filter is applied on the right). 10/15 https://t.co/xIcMJmpcpy

name: 💮🎴 MikhailAsmo 🎴💮
description: │█║│║▌║ 22 yrs old /🇫🇷/ #ActuallyAutistic / Independent Artist/ #krita & blender /Looking for work!/ I make shirts and masks  │█║│║▌║
tweet: This way its much easier to see which preset is the best for your image :). To note you can also create your own preset/LUT with the "CLUT from Before-After layers" and import other CLUT with the "Apply external CLUT" filter (all in the color category) 9/15

name: 💮🎴 MikhailAsmo 🎴💮
description: │█║│║▌║ 22 yrs old /🇫🇷/ #ActuallyAutistic / Independent Artist/ #krita & blender /Looking for work!/ I make shirts and masks  │█║│║▌║
tweet: Theres in total 896 different colors preset (yes, you read that right) arranged in 20 categories. Find this too overwhelming? No problem! At the top of each preset category you will see the "All [collage]" option. This will render a collage of all the presets of the category 8/15 https://t.co/X0kELRWtFo

name: 💮🎴 MikhailAsmo 🎴💮
description: │█║│║▌║ 22 yrs old /🇫🇷/ #ActuallyAutistic / Independent Artist/ #krita & blender /Looking for work!/ I make shirts and masks  │█║│║▌║
tweet: Next is the Simulate film/Color Presets Filter (Color Category). This is basically a collection of LUTs (if you dont know what it is instead think of it as a collection of instagram filters). Really good for tweaking colors! 7/15 https://t.co/0q6K5pN0UD

name: 💮🎴 MikhailAsmo 🎴💮
description: │█║│║▌║ 22 yrs old /🇫🇷/ #ActuallyAutistic / Independent Artist/ #krita & blender /Looking for work!/ I make shirts and masks  │█║│║▌║
tweet: Im not going to cover all of them in depth (it will be for another thread), if you want to learn how to use them instead go to Davird Revoy's YT channel! 6 /15 https://t.co/PRfMrLUZda

name: 💮🎴 MikhailAsmo 🎴💮

tweet: As you can see my lineart is very messy but the coloration works just fine.  You also dont need to close gaps in your lineart, the filter works either way. There's different algorithms available, they all have their strengths and weaknesses 5/15

name: 💮🎴 MikhailAsmo 🎴💮
